        "content": "<p>It was pointed out on the Discord that <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Function.combine#doc\">docs4#Function.combine</a> is not as universe polymorphic as one might expect, because of <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/849b08766214b9c0e277abcdba75f7d46bd975db/Mathlib/Init/Function.lean#L15\">this line</a>. Is this intentional (some sort of monad-related reason or something?)</p>",
        "id": 361990950,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1685377473
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this is why I don't like <code>variable</code></p>",
        "id": 361991266,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1685377591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in the context of <code>combine</code> it doesn't seem intentional</p>",
        "id": 361991346,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1685377613
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>is it like this in mathlib3?</p>",
        "id": 361991365,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1685377619
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes (edit: but in lean3 core, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/function.combine\">docs#function.combine</a>)</p>",
        "id": 361991472,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1685377655
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think <code>variable</code> is the culprit here; I would guess someone copied and pasted types and got fed up of writing universe variables.</p>",
        "id": 361991591,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1685377688
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At least in Lean3 you could write <code>variables {A B C D E : Type*}</code> and have it do the right thing; in lean 4 you have to deal with the fact that two types may accidentally be assigned the same universe</p>",
        "id": 361991737,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1685377752
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's a PR to change that subscript in the universe variable: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/4474\">mathlib4#4474</a></p>",
        "id": 361991990,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1685377848
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It only affects <code>Function.combine</code></p>",
        "id": 361992097,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1685377900
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This <code>ζ : Sort u₁</code> was also present in Lean 3 (in core)</p>",
        "id": 361992596,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1685378082
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Indeed it was discovered in Lean 3 and then it was noted that it had been carefully ported to Lean 4 :-)</p>",
